🛡️ Stay Safe Online – Prevention Checklist

* Do not click on suspicious links in emails or messages
* Always verify the sender’s email address before trusting any message
* Avoid sharing personal information like passwords or OTPs online
* Use strong and unique passwords for different accounts
* Enable two-factor authentication for extra security
* Check for “https://” in website URLs before entering details
* Do not download files or attachments from unknown sources
* Keep your device and apps updated regularly
* Be cautious of urgent or threatening messages asking for quick action
* Log out from accounts when using shared or public devices

🚨 Reporting Cybercrime

* Report incidents at: cybercrime.gov.in
* Call helpline: 1930
